The paper is about a new dataset for Chinese Machine Reading Comprehension, which falls under the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The dataset is based on Wikipedia paragraphs, which suggests information retrieval (cs.IR) may also be relevant. Finally, the paper mentions a challenge set that requires multi-sentence inference, which could involve neural networks (cs.NE).
